\section{Athematic verbs}

Athematic verbs are divided into two inflectional classes for convenience:
A1 and A2.

\subsection{Class A1}

Class A1 encompasses thematic verbs that end in \lan{-mi} in the
first person present, like \lan{denati}. These verbs are grouped with athematic
verbs because the endings are identical to athematic verbs, and distinct from
all the thematic verbs discussed in section \ref{sec:thematic-verbs}. Some
examples of A1 verbs are:
\begin{multicols}{2}
\begin{itemize}
	\item \lan{airáti} (\V): to protect
	\item \lan{andjóti} (\V): to end, to finish
	\item \lan{armáti} (\V): to pity
	\item \lan{arnóti} (\V): to harvest, to reap
